[Course_Description]
The Panasonic Lumix GH5 is a powerful camera packed with an assortment of cool features. In this course, learn how to get the most out of your GH5, whether you're shooting still photographs, video, or both. Joseph PhotoJoseph Linaschke walks through different GH5 features, explaining how and when to use them, and offering insights on how to fit them into your personal workflow. He familiarizes you with the camera's body, buttons, and dials, as well as a few features that are unique to the GH5, such as the new joystick and HDMI cable holder. He also covers alternative shooting modes, the menu and autofocus systems, and the fundamentals of capturing video and audio on the GH5. To wrap up, he goes into the camera's wireless functions, explaining how to leverage its built-in Bluetooth and Wi-Fi functionality for GPS tracking, remote control, and more.